<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

<title>About | PanorOmics</title>

<style>
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}

body{
  background:#020817;
  color:white;
  font-family:Inter,Arial,sans-serif;
  overflow-x:hidden;
}

.page{
  padding:72px 7% 42px;
}

.back{
  color:#3b82f6;
  text-decoration:none;
  font-size:.88rem;
  font-weight:700;
}

.hero{
  margin-top:34px;
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  gap:34px;
  align-items:center;
}

h1{
  font-size:clamp(2.15rem,3.7vw,3.5rem);
  line-height:1;
  letter-spacing:-.05em;
}

h1 span,
h2 span{
  color:#3b82f6;
}

p{
  margin-top:18px;
  color:#cbd5e1;
  font-size:.93rem;
  line-height:1.65;
  max-width:720px;
}

.video-box{
  border-radius:22px;
  overflow:hidden;
  border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.14);
  box-shadow:0 0 50px rgba(37,99,235,.12);
}

video{
  width:100%;
  display:block;
  object-fit:cover;
}

.section{
  padding:34px 0;
  border-top:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.08);
}

h2{
  font-size:clamp(1.55rem,2.5vw,2.35rem);
  line-height:1.08;
  margin-bottom:12px;
  letter-spacing:-.04em;
}

.statement{
  font-size:clamp(1.15rem,2vw,1.65rem);
  line-height:1.45;
  max-width:1050px;
  color:#e5edff;
  font-weight:600;
}

.cta{
  display:inline-flex;
  margin-top:18px;
  color:#3b82f6;
  text-decoration:none;
  font-size:.9rem;
  font-weight:700;
}

.cta:hover{
  color:#60a5fa;
}

@media(max-width:900px){
  .hero{grid-template-columns:1fr}
  .page{padding:64px 20px 36px}
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<main class="page">

  <a class="back" href="/">← Back to PanorOmics</a>

  <section class="hero">

    <div>
      <h1>About PanorOmics: <span>Reimagining Omics Sciences</span></h1>

      <p>
        PanorOmics integrates systems biology, multi-omics sciences, artificial
        intelligence, translational biotechnology, and integrative sciences into
        a unified framework for discovery, education, precision medicine, and
        next-generation biomedical innovation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="video-box">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline>
        <source src="/3_About_PanorOmics.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
    </div>

  </section>

  <section class="section">

    <p class="statement">
      PanorOmics is an emerging integrative framework that unifies molecular biology,
      computational intelligence, biotechnology, and human health into a connected
      model of scientific discovery.
    </p>

  </section>

  <section class="section">

    <h2>Systems <span>Biology</span></h2>

    <p>
      We view life as an interconnected system of genes, regulatory programs,
      proteins, metabolites, cells, tissues, environments, and phenotypes.
      This systems-level view helps connect biological complexity to disease,
      adaptation, and translational discovery.
    </p>

    <a class="cta" href="/research">Learn more about systems biology →</a>

  </section>

  <section class="section">

    <h2>Multi-Omics <span>Sciences</span></h2>

    <p>
      PanorOmics connects genomics, transcriptomics, proteomics, metabolomics,
      lipidomics, and epigenomics into a unified scientific language for
      understanding biological function across molecular layers.
    </p>

    <a class="cta" href="/genomics">Explore omics sciences →</a>

  </section>

  <section class="section">

    <h2>Artificial Intelligence & <span>Translational Biotechnology</span></h2>

    <p>
      Artificial intelligence and computational biology help transform complex
      biological data into insight. PanorOmics connects these approaches with
      translational biotechnology to support discovery, precision medicine,
      biomarker development, and biomedical innovation.
    </p>

    <a class="cta" href="/platforms">Discover AI-driven biomedical innovation →</a>

  </section>

  <section class="section">

    <h2>Education & <span>Accessible Knowledge</span></h2>

    <p>
      PanorOmics believes scientific knowledge should be visually accessible,
      interdisciplinary, and globally connected. Our goal is to make omics
      sciences clearer, more teachable, and more useful for the next generation
      of biology, biotechnology, and medicine.
    </p>

    <a class="cta" href="/education">Learn more about education and accessibility →</a>

  </section>

</main>

</body>
</html>
